Program: Last Word
Title: Marcus Klingberg, William McIlvanney, Setsuko Hara, Joel Elkes and John Peel
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b06r8gmx
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 13 Dec 2015
Matthew Bannister on The Israeli chemical weapons expert Marcus Klingberg, who was revealed to have been spying for the Soviet Union. The Scottish writer William McIlvanney, best known for his Jack Laidlaw crime novels. Val McDermid pays tribute. Setsuko Hara, one of Japan's most popular film actresses. Joel Elkes, the pharmacologist who pioneered the use of drugs to treat schizophrenia. And John Peel, the anthropologist who studied Nigeria's Yoruba people. Show less